---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title={"Timeline"}
  pageIcon={"fa-solid fa-timeline"}
  eyebrow={"Journey"}
  lede={"A draft structure of professional, personal, and creative milestones — and how they connect."}
>
<ol class="timeline">
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-desktop" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Early technology and support</span></h3>
    <p>
      My technical background began with early IT support, desktop environments, databases,
      documentation, and user support. This period helped build a strong foundation in
      troubleshooting, communication, and practical problem solving.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-computer" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Shadow Computers</span></h3>
    <p>
      Shadow Computers began in the early 2000s as part-time technical support and website work
      for friends and friends-of-friends. It gradually evolved into a long-running side business
      covering hosting, email, Microsoft 365, DNS, infrastructure support, websites, migrations,
      and client training.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Professional software &amp; infrastructure work</span></h3>
    <p>
      Over time, my professional career moved through support, infrastructure, web development,
      database systems, legacy platforms, and modern software engineering. That progression
      shaped how I think about sustainability, maintainability, and the long-term realities of
      running production systems.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-people-group" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Star Trek Online and online communities</span></h3>
    <p>
      Star Trek Online became a gateway into MMORPGs, online communities, podcasting,
      livestreaming, moderation, and community-driven content creation. It also became a major
      influence behind STO Info and many later creative and technical projects.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-microphone-lines" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Podcasting and Holosuite Media</span></h3>
    <p>
      Podcasting grew out of Star Trek Online and wider fandom communities. Over time, this
      expanded into hosting, production, audio engineering, livestreaming, publishing workflows,
      automation, creator support, and community management.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-person-running" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Running (2017–2020)</span></h3>
    <p>
      In 2017, after years of inactivity and health issues, I began a running journey that took
      me from walking parkrun to half marathons, marathons, trail races, and a 50km ultra
      marathon. Injuries eventually led to retiring from running in 2020, but the experience
      permanently changed how I think about perseverance, community, and long-term goals.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-star" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>STO Info</span></h3>
    <p>
      STO Info became one of my largest ongoing personal engineering projects, combining Star
      Trek Online, community tooling, Angular, NestJS, PostgreSQL, Cloudflare, GitHub Actions,
      observability, security, and long-term application architecture.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>
      <i class="fa-solid fa-dice-d20" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Roll20, D&amp;D and Midnight Realm</span></h3>
    <p>
      Dungeons &amp; Dragons and Roll20 became major creative and technical outlets, combining
      storytelling, automation, accessibility, UI/UX, and systems design. Projects include
      Condition Tracker, Swap Token Positions, Aura/Tint HealthColors, and Midnight Realm.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

